Dockerfile integration for all dgxarley sgl-kernel patches.

Structural changes to container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly:

1. Five new ARGs near the top of the builder stage:
     APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_ARCH_PRUNE       default 1 — arch list prune
     APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_DISABLE_FA3      default 1 — FA3 disable
     APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_SM90_TARGET default 1 — sm90 target skip
     APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_FLASHMLA    default 1 — flashmla_ops target skip
     APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG      default 0 — sm121 gemm_op.run
                                                   post-launch error check
   The first four are every-build optimizations and default to ON. The
   fifth is a diagnostic for CUTLASS sm120 GEMM template iteration work
   and stays OFF by default.

2. Add `patch` to the apt-get install list. The base image
   (scitrera/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev) does not ship the `patch` binary.

3. MOVE the sglang Python package install (`uv pip install ./python`)
   from its original early position to the end of the builder stage,
   right before stages/directory_split2.sh runs.

4. EARLY patch application for the sgl-kernel CMakeLists edits. Four
   patches (arch-prune, disable-fa3, skip-sm90-target, skip-flashmla)
   MUST be applied BEFORE the `uv build --wheel` of sgl-kernel because
   they edit sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt which is read at CMake configure
   time. Each independently gated by a build-arg.

5. LATE patch application for sgl-kernel-sm121.patch + the optional
   sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch (post-launch error diagnostic). Both
   target the JIT-compiled nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh header. Placing
   these late keeps iteration fast — changing either patch only
   invalidates the final layers, not the expensive sgl-kernel wheel
   build.

6. Add runtime debug/init tooling to the RUNTIME stage apt list (the
   one that lands in the final serving image, NOT the builder stage):
   tini, iproute2, iputils-ping, net-tools, ethtool. These give the
   served SGLang pods an init binary plus in-pod network diagnostics
   (ip/ping/ifconfig/ethtool) — useful for QSFP/RoCE/VF debugging. curl
   is already present in the runtime list, so it is not re-added.

Idempotency: Every patch application is preceded by a dry-run so
upstream drift fails immediately with a clear diagnostic instead of
producing a half-patched image. Post-apply `grep -q '<marker>'` calls
act as positive verification that the patch text actually landed in
the target file.

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly in the local
clone of scitrera/cuda-containers. The sm121 branch in that clone
carries this patch; see scripts/build_sm121_image.sh.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -12,6 +12,20 @@
 ARG SGLANG_VERSION=""
 ARG SGLANG_REF="main"
 ARG BUILD_JOBS=2
+# dgxarley sm121 build-time toggles — every sgl-kernel optimization patch
+# defaults to ON. The build script exposes disable switches for each:
+#   --no-arch-prune          sets APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_ARCH_PRUNE=0
+#   --keep-fa3               sets APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_DISABLE_FA3=0
+#   --keep-sm90-target       sets APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_SM90_TARGET=0
+#   --keep-flashmla          sets APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_FLASHMLA=0
+#   --sm121-debug            sets APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG=1
+# sm121-debug is OPT-IN (default 0); all four optimization patches default
+# to ON. Runtime-toggled via SGL_SM121_DEBUG_CUTLASS env var on the pod.
+ARG APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_ARCH_PRUNE=1
+ARG APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_DISABLE_FA3=1
+ARG APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_SM90_TARGET=1
+ARG APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_FLASHMLA=1
+ARG APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG=0
 ARG CUDA_ARCHITECTURES=121
 ARG TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST="12.1a"
 ARG NVCC_GENCODE="-gencode=arch=compute_121,code=sm_121"
@@ -30,6 +44,7 @@
         python3-pip \
         python3-dev \
         git \
+        patch \
         wget \
         ccache \
         libcudnn9-cuda-13 \
@@ -95,9 +110,53 @@
 ENV SETUPTOOLS_SCM_PRETEND_VERSION_FOR_SGLANG=${SGLANG_VERSION} \
     SETUPTOOLS_SCM_PRETEND_VERSION=${SGLANG_VERSION}
 
-# Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch)
-RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
-    uv pip install --no-build-isolation --no-deps ./python
+# dgxarley: sgl-kernel source patches (arch prune + FA3 disable +
+# sm90 target skip + flashmla skip). All four MUST be applied BEFORE
+# the sgl-kernel wheel build below, because they edit sgl-kernel/
+# CMakeLists.txt which is read at CMake configure time. Each patch is
+# independently gated by a build-arg so any combination is valid.
+#
+# Layer-cache consequence: changing ANY of these patches invalidates
+# this RUN layer and the sgl-kernel wheel build downstream. Unavoidable —
+# these patches reshape CMake inputs. The late *-sm121*.patches for
+# the JIT header stay in a much later layer for fast iteration.
+COPY patches/sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch /tmp/sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch
+COPY patches/sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch /tmp/sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch
+COPY patches/sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch /tmp/sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch
+COPY patches/sgl-kernel-skip-flashmla.patch /tmp/sgl-kernel-skip-flashmla.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang; \
+    if [ "${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_ARCH_PRUNE}" = "1" ]; then \
+        echo "=== Applying sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch ==="; \
+        patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch; \
+        patch -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch; \
+        grep -q 'dgxarley sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch' sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt; \
+    else \
+        echo "=== Skipping sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_ARCH_PRUNE=${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_ARCH_PRUNE}) ==="; \
+    fi; \
+    if [ "${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_DISABLE_FA3}" = "1" ]; then \
+        echo "=== Applying sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch ==="; \
+        patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch; \
+        patch -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch; \
+        grep -q 'dgxarley sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch' sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt; \
+    else \
+        echo "=== Skipping sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_DISABLE_FA3=${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_DISABLE_FA3}) ==="; \
+    fi; \
+    if [ "${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_SM90_TARGET}" = "1" ]; then \
+        echo "=== Applying sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch ==="; \
+        patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch; \
+        patch -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch; \
+        grep -q 'dgxarley sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch' sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt; \
+    else \
+        echo "=== Skipping sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_SM90_TARGET=${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_SM90_TARGET}) ==="; \
+    fi; \
+    if [ "${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_FLASHMLA}" = "1" ]; then \
+        echo "=== Applying sgl-kernel-skip-flashmla.patch ==="; \
+        patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-skip-flashmla.patch; \
+        patch -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-skip-flashmla.patch; \
+        grep -q 'dgxarley sgl-kernel-skip-flashmla.patch' sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt; \
+    else \
+        echo "=== Skipping sgl-kernel-skip-flashmla.patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_FLASHMLA=${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SKIP_FLASHMLA}) ==="; \
+    fi
 
 # Copy any pre-built sgl-kernel wheels from build context (may be empty)
 COPY wheel-cache/ /data/wheel-cache/
@@ -185,6 +244,46 @@
         uv pip install -U transformers --pre; \
     fi
 
+# SM121 (DGX Spark GB10) shared memory fix for cutlass_moe_fp4.
+# Patches run_fp4_blockwise_scaled_group_mm_sm120() in the JIT-compiled
+# nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh to use KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedCooperative
+# + ThreadBlockShape<_128,_64,_128>, bringing mainloop SMEM below the
+# 99 KiB SM121 budget. See patches/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch header and
+# NVIDIA/cutlass#3144 for the verified SMEM numbers and root cause.
+#
+# Placed LATE in the builder stage (after sgl-kernel build + flashinfer +
+# transformers install) so that iterating on the patch content does not
+# invalidate the expensive sgl-kernel build layer. The .cuh is a JIT
+# header compiled via nvrtc at runtime, so it only needs to be present
+# in the installed sglang Python package, not in the sgl-kernel C++ build.
+#
+# Optional sm121-debug patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG=1) stacks on
+# top of the primary patch and inserts a post-gemm_op.run() error check
+# gated by the SGL_SM121_DEBUG_CUTLASS runtime env var.
+COPY patches/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch
+COPY patches/sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang && \
+    patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch && \
+    patch -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch && \
+    grep -q 'KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedCooperative' python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh && \
+    grep -q 'collective::StageCount<2>' python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh && \
+    echo 'SM121 sgl-kernel patch applied successfully'; \
+    if [ "${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG}" = "1" ]; then \
+        echo "=== Applying sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch ==="; \
+        patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch; \
+        patch -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch; \
+        grep -q 'dgxarley sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch' python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh; \
+        echo 'SM121 debug patch applied successfully'; \
+    else \
+        echo "=== Skipping sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG=${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG}) ==="; \
+    fi
+
+# Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch).
+# Moved here from its original early-stage location so the installed
+# dist-packages picks up the patched nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh above.
+RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
+    uv pip install --no-build-isolation --no-deps ./python
+
 # Break up dist-packages into smaller layers to avoid hitting Docker layer size limits
 COPY stages/directory_split2.sh /opt/directory_split2.sh
 RUN chmod +x /opt/directory_split2.sh && \
@@ -219,6 +219,11 @@ RUN apt update && \
     libibverbs-dev \
     rdma-core \
     libxcb1 \
+    tini \
+    iproute2 \
+    iputils-ping \
+    net-tools \
+    ethtool \
     && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/* && \
     pip install uv && (pip uninstall -y flash-attn || true)
